# Model Selection

Always follow this rule when choosing which model to use:

| Mode | Model |
|------|-------|
| Planning, research, reviewing, auditing, multi-pass analysis | **claude-opus-4-6** (Opus 4.6) |
| Building, executing, implementing, editing files, running commands | **claude-sonnet-4-6** (Sonnet 4.6) |

- Use **Opus 4.6** when in Plan mode, doing deep analysis, or reviewing code for correctness.
- Use **Sonnet 4.6** when in Agent mode, writing code, running tests, or making file edits.
- Never substitute a different model without explicit user approval.
